16/04/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Specialised financial control bodies of Romania and the United States will co-operate in fighting corruption, said Romania's Court of Accounts Chief Dan Grosu Saguna, during a visit to Washington. 
On Tuesday (15 April), he met with representatives of the US General Accounting Office to discuss joint initiatives for sharing methodologies and financial surveillance techniques. 
(Rompres, Radio Romania - 16/04/03)
